>Description:
In Beginning Student language, if I misspell an identifier, I get the error message "name is not defined, not an argument, and not a primitive name".
As I understand it, the "not an argument" part actually means that the name doesn't match the name of any formal parameter whose scope covers the name occurrence.  As I understand the terminology, an "argument" is usually the actual value plugged into a function call, right?
So could we change the error message to say "parameter" rather than "argument"?
